#: ../../I/infinity.rst:5
msgid "infinity"
msgstr "infinity"

#: ../../I/infinity.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../I/infinity.rst:10
msgid ""
"The largest value that can be represented in a particular type of variable "
"(register, memory location, data type, whatever)."
msgstr "特定の種類の変数(レジスタ、メモリ位置、データ型、何であれ)で表現できる最大の値。"

#: ../../I/infinity.rst:12
msgid ""
"minus infinity: The smallest such value, not necessarily or even usually the"
" simple negation of plus infinity. In ``N``\\-bit twos-complement "
"arithmetic, infinity is :math:`2^{N-1}` but minus infinity is :math:`- "
"(2^{N-1}`\\, not :math:`-(2^{N-1}`\\. Note also that this is different from "
"time T equals minus infinity, which is closer to a mathematician's usage of "
"infinity."
msgstr ""
"minus infinity:そのような最小の値。必ずしも、いやたいていは、plus infinityの単純な符号反転ではない。\\ ``N``\\ "
"ビットの2の補数演算では、infinityは\\ :math:`2^{N-1}`\\ だが、minus infinityは\\ :math:`- "
"(2^{N-1}`\\ であって\\ :math:`-(2^{N-1}`\\ ではない。また、これは時刻Tがminus "
"infinityに等しいこととは異なり、後者のほうが数学者のinfinityの用法に近いことにも注意せよ。"
